\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Methods\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Study Design\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 This was a prospective, randomized, controlled, parallel-group study conducted at a tertiary care outpatient clinic over a period of 6 months. The study protocol was approved by the institutional ethics committee, and all participants provided written informed consent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Participants\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 A total of 160 adults aged 30\'9675 years with a diagnosis of essential hypertension were enrolled. Inclusion criteria included office systolic blood pressure \uc0\u8805 140 mmHg and/or diastolic blood pressure \u8805 90 mmHg, or current use of antihypertensive medication. Exclusion criteria included secondary hypertension, pregnancy, severe cardiovascular disease within the past 6 months, chronic kidney disease stage 4 or higher, and inability to use a home blood pressure device.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Randomization and Intervention\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Participants were randomized in a 1:1 ratio using a computer-generated sequence to one of two groups:\
