\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Results\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Participant Characteristics\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Of the 160 enrolled participants, 152 completed the study (HBPM group: n = 76; control group: n = 76). Baseline characteristics, including age, sex, baseline blood pressure, body mass index, and number of antihypertensive medications, were comparable between groups.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Primary Outcomes\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 At 6 months, the HBPM group demonstrated a significantly greater reduction in blood pressure compared to the control group. Mean systolic blood pressure decreased by 14.6 \'b1 9.3 mmHg in the HBPM group versus 7.2 \'b1 8.1 mmHg in the control group (p < 0.001). Mean diastolic blood pressure decreased by 8.9 \'b1 6.2 mmHg versus 4.1 \'b1 5.4 mmHg, respectively (p < 0.001).\
A higher proportion of participants in the HBPM group achieved target blood pressure (<130/80 mmHg) compared to the control group (62% vs. 38%, p = 0.002).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Secondary Outcomes\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Medication adherence scores improved significantly in the HBPM group, with mean MMAS-8 scores increasing from 6.1 to 7.4, compared to a smaller increase in the control group (6.2 to 6.6; p < 0.01). Patient satisfaction scores were also significantly higher in the intervention group.\
The HBPM group experienced more frequent but appropriate antihypertensive medication adjustments, suggesting improved clinical decision-making based on more comprehensive blood pressure data.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Adverse Events\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 No serious adverse events were reported. Minor issues included initial anxiety related to self-measurement in a small number of participants, which resolved after further education.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
